text: Fulwood A.F.C. was an English association football club from Sheffield, South Yorkshire. The club competed in the FA Amateur Cup during the 1920s, and won the South Yorkshire Amateur League in 1938, 1939 and 1947 ==References== Category:Defunct football clubs in England Category:Defunct football clubs in South Yorkshire Category:South Yorkshire Amateur Football League Category:Sheffield Amateur League Category:Hatchard League
